= Terminal =
To change the <u>keyboard layout</u>.

<pre>
sudo dpkg-reconfigure console-data

## French keyboards:
## Perhaps an upstream bug.
## ( http://free.nchc.org.tw/clonezilla-live/stable/Known-issues-Clonezilla-live.txt )
## If you are using French Keymap, Remember to use "Select keymap from full list"
## 1. Select keymap from full list
## 2. pc / azerty / French / Same as X11 (latin 9) /Standard

## Alternative 1:
sudo dpkg-reconfigure keyboard-configuration
## Make reconfigured keyboard-configuration changes affect.
setupcon

## Alternative 2:
edit /etc/default/keyboard

## Alternative 3 (temporary until reboot):
setxkbmap de
</pre>

= Non-Qubes-Whonix =
== Desktop Environment (KDE) ==
[[Non-Qubes-Whonix]] only!

Use one of the following methods to change the <u>keyboard layout</u> from the default "us" to something else.

=== Keyboard Search ===
[[Non-Qubes-Whonix]] only!

* <code>Start menu button</code> -> <code>search</code> -> <code>keyboard</code> -> <code>layout</code> -> <code>add yours and remove the default</code>

=== System Settings ===
[[Non-Qubes-Whonix]] only!

# <code>KDE</code>
# <code>Start menu button</code>
# <code>Applications</code> 
# <code>Settings</code> 
# <code>System Settings</code> 
# <code>input devices</code> 
# <code>layout</code> 
# <code>add yours and remove the default</code> 
# <code>apply</code>

The procedure is complete.

= Qubes-Whonix =

== Desktop Environment ==

Instead of applying [https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/language-localization/ language localization input] on a per VM basis, the following [https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc/pull/340/commits/eea10c71415f93bbf9e2eae5a9ef50ffeaf06789 workaround] will correctly apply changes system-wide. <ref>Users report problems with the <code>System Tools</code> -> <code>Keyboard</code> -> <code>Layout</code> method in dom0, since the change [https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-issues/issues/1396 does not propagate to other VMs].</ref>

Also see [https://www.qubes-os.org/faq/ My keyboard layout settings are not behaving correctly. What should I do?] in the FAQ if problems are encountered.

